#---------------------------------------------------------------------- 
# JDK

Q: What is JDK?
Java (Standard Edition) Development Kit
The JDK is a development environment for building applications, applets, and components using the Java programming language.
It is used to compile Java programs
JDK includes a JRE, which in turn is used to run Java programs
!!! The 'java' command line is used to run java programs

Q: Where to find JDK?
http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk7-downloads-1880260.html
jdk-7u17-linux-x64.tar.gz
